If it is any consolation - I work at a vet clinic and when we do surgery intake for nervous pets we sit with them in their kennels, or if we need to work they will sit on our laps while we reply to emails and calls until it is time for their surgery. For most cases, we have been finding that pets have been doing really well away from their owners in the clinic after the initial anxiety when we pick them up in the car park. I hope this helps for future visits, or anyone else in the comments that worries when dropping pets off during COVID <3

Make homemade crackers!!!  It's a tradition in our family to do Crackers. (We live in Canada but my Grandma (dads mom) is from England).
